  "text": "Proof. The fact that the function W in (5.5) is positive definite on the real line implies that for each τ the integral operator T τ in (1.1) is strictly positive. Hence k is an accelerant on each interval [−T, T]. Using Theorem 4.1 in [CITATION_1] one computes that in this setting",
